document_data.name: Warehouse District
document_data.mainbody: The '''Warehouse District''' of [[Port Nyanzaru]] was a section of the city's [[Port Nyanzaru/Harbor Ward|Harbor Ward]] where goods being shipped into or out of the city were stored.
document_data.Description: The district was characterized by its canals that separated the rows of warehouses. Full-size merchant ships could be towed through these canals by [[dinosaur]]s, allowing for the vessels to be brought straight to the sites where their cargo was to be loaded or unloaded. Because traffic jams were a notable concern with this arrangement, organizing this towing operation was one of the key responsibilities of Port Nyzanzaru's harbormaster.
document_data.Geography: The Warehouse District was located in central Port Nyanzaru, east of the drydocks and west of the public docks.
document_data.History: In the late 15{{th}} century [[DR]], the harbormaster in charge of traffic management in the Warehouse District was [[Zindar]].
